  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the following limits. (15) 
        <ol>
          <li><me>
           \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{x^2 + x - 2}{x^2 - 3x + 2}
         </me></li>
         <li><me>
           \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{x^2 + x - 6}{x^2 + 2x - 8}
         </me></li>
         <li><me>
           \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{\frac{1}{x^2} - 1}{x-1}
         </me></li>
         <li><me>
           \lim_{x \rightarrow 2} \frac{x^2 - 5x + 7}{x^2 - 4x + 4}
         </me></li>
         <li><me>
           \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin^2 x}{x^2 - 1}
         </me></li>
       </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, find a value of <m>a</m>
        that makes the function continuous or demonstrate that no
        value of <m>a</m> is possible. (12) 
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
              x^2 - 3 \amp x \lt 1 \\
              \frac{a}{x} \amp x \geq 1 
            \end{matrix} \right.
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
              \sin (ax) \amp x \lt 0 \\
              x^2 + 4 \amp x \geq 0
            \end{matrix} \right.
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            (x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
              \ln x \amp x \gt e \\
              x + a \amp x \leq e
            \end{matrix} \right.
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
